message.content: cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR. The paper deals with the task of Visual Question Answering (VQA), which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also proposes a new evaluation metric, which involves statistical analysis and machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of textual data, which could also fit into the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
